Her attention to detail and style catered to the Prep life. The watch designs started in a small jewelry store in Austria on the famous fashion street of Schloss Mirabel. We are carrying on the tradition started by Bertha Gleisner. Today's watch offers precision watch movements; retro classic dial designs and caters to making life look easy without trying. Bertha engraved all the watch case-backs "with love" and her name. We decided to continue the tradition. Engraved on the case back of every Bertha watch are the words "with love." It's a simple phrase that, like the 1920s prep fashion beloved by Bertha's designers, takes something sophisticated and makes it look effortless. Prep fashion took the high-minded veneer of the Ivy League and made it look warm, welcoming, and even a bit glamorous. Bertha's designers infuse that attitude into each watch, carefully balancing embellishments such as engraved dials, crystal markers, and croco leather bands to craft deceptively layered looks. This approach carries through to jewelry pieces such as bracelets, necklaces, and wizards' scepters.
